Stacked bar chart:

Filled bar chart: The above two charts show the educational attainment by race in Santa Clara county (CA) for individuals 25 and older. In this particular county, there are a disproportionate number of individuals who self-identify as ‘Asian alone’ with Bachelor’s degrees, compared to the number of individuals of other races with bachelor’s degrees. Since this data is only for those 25 and up, these stats may change as current students graduate.

Filled bar chart:

The above two charts show the educational attainment by ethnicity in Santa Clara county (CA) for individuals 25 and older. I’m not sure if this dataset is incorrect since it shows the majority of households are headed by a self-identified Latinx individual. Assuming this data is correct, higher levels of educational attainment are disproportionately representedd by Latinx households.
